Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Cut and hollow out bowl in loaf to within 1 inch of all sides, leaving center intact. Cut loaf center into bite-size dippers. Brush cut surfaces of bowl and dippers with oil. Arrange bowl cut side up and dippers on baking sheet. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Meanwhile, cook and stir sausage over medium-high heat 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked; drain. Stir in salsa and heat until hot. Place bowl on platter and spoon in salsa mixture. Sprinkle with onions. Serve with dippers and veggies.